1 Update annotations from google drive

Code 
# read data
ann_folder <- drive_find(pattern = "raven_selections", type = "folder")

# list family folders
fam_folders <- drive_ls(ann_folder)

# list files
anns_ls <- lapply(1:nrow(fam_folders), function(x) drive_ls(fam_folders$id[1]))

all_ans <- do.call(rbind, anns_ls)

owd <- getwd()

setwd("./data/processed/annotations")

# copy locally new files found in google drive
new_files <- sapply(1:nrow(all_ans), function(x) {

    if (!file.exists(all_ans$name[x])) {

        drive_download(all_ans$id[x])

        out <- TRUE

    } else out <- FALSE

    return(out)
})

setwd(owd)


new_file_count <- sum(new_files)

if (new_file_count > 0) print(paste(new_file_count, "new annotations file(s) found"))

Code 
rec_data <- read_sheet("https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/16ukhyf37hm13f1FXB2JQ-tCfHoxXy2qj_TX2xWvTVu8/edit#gid=148139271")

anns <- imp_raven(path = "./data/processed/annotations", all.data = TRUE,
    warbler.format = TRUE, name.from.file = TRUE, ext.case = "lower",
    pb = FALSE)

ann_files <- unique(c(anns$selec.file, unlist(.Options$Rraven)))

ann_files <- data.frame(file = ann_files)

ann_files$species <- gsub("_", " ", sapply(strsplit(ann_files$file,
    "-"), "[", 1))


# all(ann_files$species %in% rec_data$species)

ann_files$family <- sapply(ann_files$species, function(x) rec_data$family[rec_data$species ==
    x][1])

# get those in which the name doesnt match the expected
weird_files <- ann_files[!grepl("Table.1.selections.txt", ann_files$file) |
    ann_files$file %in% unlist(.Options$Rraven), ]

weird_files$problem <- "file name"
weird_files$problem[weird_files$file %in% unlist(.Options$Rraven)] <- "Empty file"

# keep only those with 'good' names
ann_files <- ann_files[!ann_files$file %in% weird_files$file, ]

# counts per family
fam_count <- aggregate(species ~ family, data = rec_data, length)
names(fam_count)[2] <- "total"

fam_count$annotated <- sapply(fam_count$family, function(x) sum(ann_files$family ==
    x))

fam_count$prop.annotated <- round(fam_count$annotated/fam_count$total,
    2)

fam_count$assinged.to <- sapply(fam_count$family, function(x) paste(unique(rec_data$assigned_to[rec_data$family ==
    x]), collapse = "/"))

fam_count$assinged.to[fam_count$assinged.to == "NA"] <- "not assigned"

weird_files$assinged.to <- sapply(weird_files$family, function(x) paste(unique(rec_data$assigned_to[rec_data$family ==
    x]), collapse = "/"))

problematic_sels <- cs[cs$check.res != "OK", ]

# weird duration or frequency range
long_anns <- ok_anns[ok_anns$end - ok_anns$start > 1, ]
long_anns$check.res <- "longer than 1 s"

broad_anns <- ok_anns[ok_anns$top.freq - ok_anns$bottom.freq > 10,
    ]
broad_anns$check.res <- "frequency range wider than 10 kHz"

problematic_sels <- rbind(problematic_sels, long_anns, broad_anns)

problematic_sels <- problematic_sels[, c("sound.files", "family",
    "assinged.to", "selec", "check.res")]

4.1 Created annotated spectrograms

Code 
# create folders for each family for(i in
# unique(rec_data$family))
# dir.create(file.path('./data/processed/annotated_spectrograms',
# i))

out <- warbleR:::pblapply_wrblr_int(sort(unique(ok_anns$sound.files)),
    pbar = TRUE, cl = 8, function(x) {
        sub_anns <- ok_anns[ok_anns$sound.files == x, ]
        frq_range <- range(c(sub_anns$bottom.freq, sub_anns$top.freq))

        frq_range[1] <- frq_range[1] - 1
        if (frq_range[1] < 0)
            frq_range[1] <- 0

        frq_range[2] <- frq_range[2] + ((frq_range[2] - frq_range[1])/3)
        if (frq_range[2] < 6)
            frq_range[2] <- 6

        if (frq_range[2] > 22.05)
            frq_range[2] <- 22.05

```{r descriptive stats, eval = TRUE}
    sum(ann_files$family == x))

    paste(unique(rec_data$assigned_to[rec_data$family == x]), collapse = "/"))
```

## Created annotated spectrograms
```{r, eval = FALSE}

# create folders for each family
# for(i in unique(rec_data$family))
#     dir.create(file.path("./data/processed/annotated_spectrograms", i))

out <- warbleR:::pblapply_wrblr_int(sort(unique(ok_anns$sound.files)), pbar = TRUE, cl = 8, function(x)
    {
    sub_anns <- ok_anns[ok_anns$sound.files == x, ]
    frq_range <- range(c(sub_anns$bottom.freq, sub_anns$top.freq))
    
    frq_range[1] <- frq_range[1] - 1
    if (frq_range[1] < 0) frq_range[1] <- 0

    frq_range[2] <- frq_range[2] + ((frq_range[2] - frq_range[1]) / 3)
    if(frq_range[2] < 6) frq_range[2] <- 6
    
    if (frq_range[2] > 22.05) frq_range[2] <- 22.05
    
    
    # print(ok_anns$family[1])
    full_spectrograms(X = sub_anns, flim = frq_range, sxrow = 4, rows = 10, ovlp = 50, collevels = seq(-100, 0, 5), parallel = 1, overwrite = TRUE, dest.path = file.path("./data/processed/annotated_spectrograms", sub_anns$family[1]), song = "song", fast.spec = TRUE, horizontal = TRUE, pb = FALSE)
    }
    )
```
